value.title: Trump nominates former Nunes aide as intelligence community inspector general
value.excerpt: President Donald Trump intends to nominate Allen Souza as the next inspector general for the intel community after firing the previous inspector general, Michael Atkinson, in April.

value.title: Pence asks governors to build confidence in vaccine
value.excerpt: Vice President Mike Pence and other federal health officials sought to impress upon governors Monday the importance of boosting confidence in an eventual coronavirus vaccine as President Donald Trump continues to suggest one will be available before the election.

value.title: Rep. Ilhan Omar on Trump's racist attack: 'This is my country'
value.excerpt: Democratic Rep. Ilhan Omar on Tuesday hit back at President Donald Trump after he disparaged her during a campaign rally, falsely implying that she's not American.

value.title: Joe Biden condemns Poland's 'LGBT-free zones'
value.excerpt: The Democratic presidential candidate shared a tweet saying such zones "have no place in the European Union or anywhere in the world."

value.title: Senate GOP report attacks Bidens with previously aired allegations of conflicts of interest

value.title: Trump and McConnell's marriage of convenience seeks its ultimate prize
value.excerpt: No one would ever say that the political marriage between Senate Majority Leader Mitch McConnell and President Donald Trump is a match made in heaven. It's nothing like that, and nothing near love.

value.title: ‘It affects virtually nobody’: Trump downplays virus threat to young people
value.excerpt: The president previously told The Washington Post’s Bob Woodward in March that Covid-19 affects “plenty of young people.”

value.title: Biden announces Cindy McCain will endorse him
value.excerpt: Cindy McCain, the widow of longtime Republican Sen. John McCain of Arizona, is set to endorse Joe Biden, the Democratic presidential nominee told donors Tuesday.

value.title: Trump's ex-Russia adviser Fiona Hill: US increasingly seen as 'object of pity'
value.excerpt: President Donald Trump's former top Russia adviser said Tuesday that the United States is increasingly seen as "an object of pity" and its standing on the world stage is eroding.

value.title: Washington Post: CIA assessment says Putin 'probably directing' efforts to interfere in 2020 election against Biden
value.excerpt: The CIA assessed in August that Russian President Vladimir Putin and his top aides "are aware of and probably directing Russia's influence operations" aimed at undermining Democratic presidential candidate Joe Biden in the 2020 election, according to a new report in The Washington Post.

value.title: Bernie Sanders Sounds Alarm on a Trump ‘Nightmare Scenario’
value.excerpt: Warning that this election is an “extremely dangerous moment” for the country, he said in an interview that he would aggressively push to try to stop President Trump from delegitimizing the vote.

value.title: Trump will go to Pittsburgh and Pence to New Hampshire as Harris visits Flint and Detroit.
value.excerpt: Delivers remarks at a campaign rally in a hangar at Pittsburgh International Airport. Afternoon — Tours small businesses that have been affected by the coronavirus pandemic in Flint, Mich. 4:30 p.m. — Participates in “Shop Talk” round-table conversation with Black men in Detroit.

value.title: Trump and Barr call NYC an 'anarchist jurisdiction' in brazen ploy to crush dissent
value.excerpt: Everything old is new again, and a glance back at 1886 proves there is a very bloody precedent for what Trump's White House is doing here.

value.title: Trump: ‘I’m so angry at Republicans’
value.excerpt: The president says his fellow Republicans have let him it down when it comes to investigating Obama and the Bidens.

value.title: Barbara Lagoa, one of Trump's top contenders for the Supreme Court
value.excerpt: President Donald Trump said he plans to select a woman to replace the late Justice Ruth Bader Ginsburg, a feminist icon who helped lead the Supreme Court's liberal wing for years. value.excerpt: President Donald Trump's former national security adviser H.R. value.title: 'Golden nuggets': Trump explains to Woodward why judges are key to his record
value.excerpt: President Donald Trump repeatedly boasted to journalist Bob Woodward about the number of judges he has appointed to the federal bench during several of their interviews for "Rage." value.title: Jeff Zucker Helped Create Donald Trump. That Show May Be Ending.
value.excerpt: The coziness between the TV executive and Mr. Trump is a Frankenstein story for the cable news era. But then the monster got away.

value.title: Pelosi won't rule out new impeachment to delay SCOTUS vote if Biden wins
value.excerpt: "Well, we have our options," Pelosi told ABC's "This Week." "We have arrows in our quiver that I’m not about to discuss right now."

value.title: Clinton: 'Superficially hypocritical' for Trump and GOP to fill Ginsburg's seat
value.excerpt: Former President Bill Clinton says it is "superficially hypocritical" for President Donald Trump and Senate Republicans to push to put a new justice on the Supreme Court before the November election.

value.title: Trump Supporters Disrupt Early Voting in Virginia
value.excerpt: A group waving Trump flags and chanting “four more years” created a commotion at a polling location in Fairfax, Va. A county official said some voters and staff members felt intimidated.

value.title: Susan Collins says Trump can nominate a justice, but Senate vote should wait until after election
value.excerpt: Republican Sen. Susan Collins on Saturday weighed in on the US Supreme Court vacancy, saying that she believes waiting until after the election is the right decision.

value.title: Behind Trump's Turkish 'bromance': Lev Parnas, oligarchs and a lucrative lobbying deal
value.excerpt: Turkey’s effort to influence the Trump White House began at the Watergate, in a meeting brokered by a figure from the Ukraine impeachment saga, Lev Parnas.

value.title: Trump's Covid-19 vaccine timeline is missing key context about logistics of herd immunity
value.excerpt: With Covid-19 continuing to ravage communities, Americans are anxious to discover a vaccine. value.title: Joe Biden mourns Ruth Bader Ginsburg and says she shouldn't be replaced until after the election
value.excerpt: Democratic presidential nominee and former Vice President Joe Biden mourned the passing of Supreme Court Justice Ruth Bader Ginsburg on Friday and demanded that voters dictate the next president before her replacement is chosen.

value.title: Rep. Engel agrees to drop Pompeo subpoena now that he has Biden documents
value.excerpt: House Foreign Affairs Chairman Eliot Engel on Friday agreed to withdraw a subpoena he had issued in July against Secretary of State Mike Pompeo after the State Department turned over more than 16,000 pages of documents the committee had sought, the panel announced.

value.title: Trump announces aid for Puerto Rico, infusing politics in an apparent play for Florida voters
value.excerpt: Polling shows Trump and Biden are tied in Florida, where thousands of Puerto Ricans relocated after Hurricane Maria.

value.title: US sending armored vehicles into Syria as Trump says 'we are out'
value.excerpt: The US military announced Friday that it is deploying armored vehicles and other military assets to Syria to protect US troops fighting ISIS amid tensions with Russia as President Donald Trump told a White House news conference that "we are out of Syria," saying the remaining US forces are there exclusively

value.title: White House tries to play defense with falsehoods about former Pence aide Troye
value.excerpt: The White House moved quickly Thursday to try to discredit Olivia Troye, the former aide to Vice President Mike Pence, after she released a video charging that President Donald Trump failed to protect the public from coronavirus and that he only cared about getting reelected.

value.title: Kamala Harris urges Black Americans to vote: ‘It’s up to us.’
value.excerpt: Senator Kamala Harris of California urged Black Americans to vote on Friday, saying it was “up to us to act” in a forceful call to action for one of the Democratic Party’s most important voting blocs.
